1. Compile the code

For many users, the default Makefiles (Makefile.ubuntu or Makefile.macos) may not function correctly.
MetaGeneMark-2 relies on certain Boost libraries, which you can find at https://www.boost.org.
Boost libraries are optional on most systems, and their installation location can vary between Linux and macOS.

1. Install the Boost libraries or the required subset, specifically:
   - headers
   - boost_program_options
   - boost_iostreams

2 . Check if the Boost libraries are accessible through the default configuration.
    If they are not accessible, set the Boost library paths in the Makefile.*.
    For an example of a path setup, see the Makefile.ubuntu: "I/usr/include/boost/"

The specific set of commands to achieve the above depends on your operating system.

Ubuntu

# install boost
sudo apt-get install libboost-all-dev
# compile the code
make -f Makefile.ubuntu

2. Installation

Copy the following files to the desired installation location:

mkdir mgm2
cp mgm2_11.mod mgm2
cp mgm2_4.mod  mgm2
cp gmhmmp2     mgm2
cp run_mgm2.pl mgm2

mv mgm2 installation_path

# ====================================================
# done

